M a l e: Protarsomeres and mesotarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 180, 181
) 0.72-0.74 mm long, fairly strongly sclerotized, symmetrical. Median lobe with elongate basal bulb, robust, not prominent articular process and ventral branch of apical process strongly inflexed, tapering and sinuate in lateral view, abruptly narrowed in apical section in dorsal view. Dorsal branches of apical process short, weakly sclerotized. Parameres wide, with large lobes, in dorsal view curved and overlapping apically. Internal sac with robust mesal tooth, bunch of long apical spines and finely denticulate structures in basal and admesal sections.
